text: Presidential elections were held in Moldova on 20 October 2024, with a runoff held on 3 November. Incumbent president Maia Sandu who won the first round and former Prosecutor General Alexandr Stoianoglo who was the runner-up ran in the runoff, with Sandu winning a majority of votes and being re-elected for a final second term. ==Notes== ==References== Category:November 2024 events Category:Presidential elections Category:2024 elections in Europe Category:2020s in Moldova Category:Politics of Moldova
title: 2024 Moldovan presidential election
